result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Kayla Michelle Williams

records.addlTxt: Branch 2 down on January 20, 2023.  Court rescheduled Doctor's Report Return hearing to January 19, 2023 at 1:30 PM.  Parties notified of court date.  Case adjourned to Branch 2, Rm 635 CH.

Defendant Kayla Michelle Williams appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Andrew Joel Golden appeared by video for Kayla Michelle Williams.  Attorney Gerald Henry Alder in court for State of Wisconsin. 

Case in court for a competency hearing.  Sworn for the State: Doctor Daniel Stabin (Examining Pyschologist).  It is the opinion of Doctor Daniel Stabin that Ms. Williams is not competent to proceed and will not be restored within the statutory period.  Closing arguments heard.  Court adopts the Doctor's findings and orders continued commitment for treatment.  Court scheduled a Return on Doctor's Report.  Case adjourned to Branch 2, Rm 635 CH.
Doctor's Report Return scheduled for January 20, 2023 at 08:30 am.

Upon request from the Defense, Court rescheduled Doctor's Report Return to October 21, 2022 at 1:30 PM.  Doctor Daniel Stabin confirmed availability for Zoom appearance.  Case adjourned to Branch 2, Rm 635 CH.
Received and Filed: Doctor's Report Dated 09-21-2022.

Competency Hearing exhibits from 08/03/2022 inventoried on this date.
Location: BOX 791

Defendant Kayla Michelle Williams in court with attorney Andrew Joel Golden.  Defendant Kayla Michelle Williams in custody.  Gerald Henry Alder appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Hearing held via Zoom.  Sworn for the State: Dr. Sanchez. Exhibit #1 received. Testimony closed. Statements by parties.
Court finds that the defendant remains incompetent to proceed at this time, but if provided with appropriate treatment, is likely to become competent within the statutory time frame. Court does not find the four Sell factors have been met for the involuntary administration of medication. Case adourned for return on doctor report, Branch 2. 


  Doctor's Report Return scheduled for October 28, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Kayla Michelle Williams in court with attorney Andrew Joel Golden.  Defendant Kayla Michelle Williams in custody.  Amanda Korin Kirklewski appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Deputy Court Clerk: cmt
Hearing held by Zoom. Doctor's report received and filed. State does not contest findings, however Defense contest findings and requests a hearing. Case scheduled for competency hearing, Branch 2.  Competency hearing scheduled for August 3, 2022 at 02:30 pm.
Due to rotation changes, Return on doctor report moved from 07-25-2022 to 07-29-2022 at 8:30 am by Zoom.
Order of Commitment for Treatment, signed

Defendant Kayla Michelle Williams in court with attorney Andrew Joel Golden.  Defendant Kayla Michelle Williams in custody.  James C Griffin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Hearing held via Zoom.   Case in court for return on doctors report.  Parties review and do not contest  Doctors Report.  Court finds the defendant lacks substantial capacity to understand court proceedings or to assist in his own defense.  Court orders proceedings suspended.   Court ordered defendant committed to the Department of Health and Family Services for Institutional Care in order to restore competency within the statutory time frame. Defendant is REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department for transportation to the designated facility.  Order of Commitment signed and filed.  Court orders case adjourned for Return of Doctor's Report in Branch 2.  Doctor's Report Return scheduled for July 28, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Forensic evaluation ordered.  INITIAL APPEARANCE NOT HELD.  Trial court to address INITIAL APPEARANCE on next court date.

Defendant Kayla Michelle Williams in court with attorney Stephen Andrew Sargent.  Defendant Kayla Michelle Williams in custody.  Sara Waldschmidt-DeSmet appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Kayla Michelle Williams appeared by video means with Attorney.  Court is advised by the defense there is reason to believe the defendant is not competent to proceed.  Pursuant to Sec. 971.14 (2) Wisconsin Statutes, Court found probable cause and ordered defendant examined by the Forensic Unit.  Order for Examination, signed and filed.   Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Childs, Branch 02.   Court ordered defendant REMANDED into custody of Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.  Commissioner tolls the time limits for the preliminary hearing.  This hearing will be streamed live on https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/c5e6133e-7164-4e97-66e6-4c87ef70fbdb  Doctor's Report Return scheduled for April 28, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
